[[Image:Georges-André Chevallaz by Erling Mandelmann.jpg|thumb|200px|Chevallaz after retiring from the Federal Council]]
'''Georges-André Chevallaz''' (7 February 1915 &ndash; 8 September 2002) was a [[Switzerland|Swiss]] historian, politician and [[member of the Swiss Federal Council]] (1974&ndash;1983).

[[Mayor of Lausanne]] since 1957 and member of the [[Swiss National Council]] since 1958, he was elected to the [[Swiss Federal Council]] on 5 December 1973 and handed over office on 31 December 1983. He was affiliated to the [[Free Democratic Party of Switzerland|Free Democratic Party]]. During his office time he held the following departments:
* [[Federal Department of Finance]] (1974&ndash;1979)
* [[Federal Military Department]] (1980&ndash;1983)

He was [[President of the Confederation (Switzerland)|President of the Confederation]] in 1980.

After retiring from the Federal Council, he presided the foundation of the [[Historical Dictionary of Switzerland]] (1988&ndash;1992).

==Works==
*''Aspects de l'agriculture vaudoise à la fin de l'Ancien Régime : la terre, le blé, les charges''; F. Rouge, Lausanne; (1949) -- thesis
* ''The challenge of neutrality : diplomacy and the defense of Switzerland''; Lexington books, Lanham (translated from ''Le défi de la neutralité'', 2001) {{ISBN|0-7391-0274-5}}
*''Histoire générale, de 1789 à nos jours''; Payot, Lausanne (1st ed., 1957)

