'''The Institute for the Study and Integration of Graphical Heritage Techniques''' (INSIGHT)''' an American computer laboratory for archaeological visualization based in [[Berkeley, California]]. INSIGHT's principal work consists of archaeological documentation projects for [[academics]], [[universities]] and [[non-governmental organizations]]. INSIGHT's work has been included in documentary films, including ''Sunken Treasures of the Nile'',<ref name="Sunken Treasures of the Nile">{{Cite web | author=National Geographic Society| publisher=National Geographic Society | title =Sunken Treasures of the Nile | date =March 1, 2010|url =http://natgeotv.com.au/tv/sunken-treasure-of-the-nile/ | accessdate =March 1, 2010 }}</ref> ''Queens of the Nile''<ref name="Queens of the Nile">{{Cite web | author=éclectic production / France 3| publisher=EuropeImages | title =Queens of the Nile | date =March 1, 2010|url =http://www.europeimages.com/programme/3345/dans-le-secret-des-reines-du-nil?userlocale=en_EN | accessdate =March 1, 2010 }}</ref> and ''Ramses II, the Great Journey''.<ref name="Ramses II, the Great Journey">{{Cite web | author=AST | publisher=AST | title =Ramses II, the Great Journey | date =March 1, 2010|url =http://www.science-television.com/en/film/1657/ramses-ii-the-great-journey/ | accessdate =March 1, 2010 }}</ref>
INSIGHT began in 1998 as the Egyptian Cultural Heritage Operation (ECHO), with the support of the Center for Design Visualization at the [[University of California at Berkeley]].
